title: Chief Complaint
content: Wrist pain after two falls over the last two days

title: HPI Spencer
content: The patient experienced two falls over the last two days: one while climbing a slide and another while falling off an electric scooter. Following both incidents, he developed pain in his left wrist, particularly with extension, which has not improved.

title: Musculoskeletal
content: Moderate soft tissue swelling of the dorsal aspect of the left wrist, mild ecchymosis, significant pain with wrist extension.

title: Imaging Results
content: X-rays of the left wrist demonstrate a dorsal distal radius fracture.

title: Plan
content: Application of a plan fractured cast.
Follow-up in two weeks for repeat X-rays and cast change.
